text.tspan: Share of women whose family planning needs are met, 2021

The proportion of women aged 15-49 years who are currently using at least one
modern contraceptive
method,
out of the total population of women who want to postpone their next pregnancy or have no more children.
Data source: Population Division, Department of Economic and Social Affairs and United Nations Population Fund
